public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    while (n!= 0) {
        int remainder = n % 3;
        if (remainder == 0) {
            return true;
        }
        n /= 3;
    }
    return false;
}
```

This solution uses a while loop to repeatedly divide `n` by 3. If the remainder of the division is 0, then we know that n is a power of three. If the remainder of the division is not 0, then we continue dividing by 3 until n is equal to 0. If n is not equal to 0 at the end of the loop, then we return false.

This solution has a time complexity of O(log n) since we are dividing by 3 at most log n times.

